1525
01:05:27,186 --> 01:05:29,686
length scales smaller than what you can see,

1526
01:05:29,686 --> 01:05:31,686
it has an effective output

1527
01:05:31,686 --> 01:05:34,686
which is the sum of all that stuff

1528
01:05:34,686 --> 01:05:36,686
which you lump together.

1529
01:05:36,686 --> 01:05:38,686
You lump it together into

1530
01:05:38,686 --> 01:05:40,686
a single thing that you call

1531
01:05:40,686 --> 01:05:43,686
the mass squared over two.

1532
01:05:44,686 --> 01:05:47,686
So the physical mass squared, the thing you measure

1533
01:05:47,686 --> 01:05:49,186
when you do an experiment

1534
01:05:49,186 --> 01:05:50,686
that, let's say, relatively low energy,

1535
01:05:50,686 --> 01:05:53,686
that doesn't involve really, really small distances,

1536
01:05:53,686 --> 01:05:55,686
is this renormalized mass here, which

1537
01:05:55,686 --> 01:05:57,686
