01:21:55,686 --> 01:21:58,686
field can be absorbed and reemitted,

1885
01:21:58,686 --> 01:22:00,686
or, sorry, emitted and reabsorbed.

1886
01:22:00,686 --> 01:22:02,686
What kind of thing does that make?

1887
01:22:02,686 --> 01:22:04,686
Can that make left go to right?

1888
01:22:04,686 --> 01:22:07,186
No, it can't, because the

1889
01:22:07,186 --> 01:22:09,686
scalar emission here always takes left,

1890
01:22:09,686 --> 01:22:14,686
where is it, always takes left to right,

1891
01:22:14,686 --> 01:22:16,686
or right to left.

1892
01:22:16,686 --> 01:22:17,686
This is the scalar particle here.

1893
01:22:18,686 --> 01:22:23,686
The scalar particle always involves transition,

1894
01:22:23,686 --> 01:22:25,186
and so here you can go

1895
01:22:25,186 --> 01:22:26,686
from left to right all right,

1896
01:22:26,686 --> 01:22:28,686
but then in the reabsorption here

1897
01:22:28,686 --> 01:22:30,686
you're going to go back to left.

1898
01:22:30,686 --> 01:22:32,686
And if you think about it,

1899
01:22:32,686 --> 01:22:36,686
no matter how complicated the Feynman diagram is,

1900
01:22:36,686 --> 01:22:41,686
it's always going to involve an even number of vertices,

1901
01:22:41,686 --> 01:22:44,686
because it involves an even number of vertices.

1902
01:22:44,686 --> 01:22:46,686
Whatever gets emitted must get reabsorbed.

1903
01:22:46,686 --> 01:22:47,686
That's all it comes down to.

1904
01:22:47,686 --> 01:22:50,686
If it's going to be just electron goes to electron,

1905
01:22:50,686 --> 01:22:52,686
whatever gets emitted must get reabsorbed,

1906
01:22:52,686 --> 01:22:54,686
the number of vertices must be even,

1907
01:22:54,686 --> 01:22:57,686
and if the number of vertices is even from this,

1908
01:22:57,686 --> 01:23:04,686
then you can't make left go to right.

1909
01:23:04,686 --> 01:23:06,686
And so again, scalar emission

1910
01:23:06,686 --> 01:23:08,686
and absorption will have no effect

1911
01:23:08,686 --> 01:23:10,186
on the mass of the

1912
01:23:10,186 --> 01:23:11,686
electron if it starts from zero.

1913
01:23:11,686 --> 01:23:14,186
Okay, can you ever get a

1914
01:23:14,186 --> 01:23:16,686
shift of the mass of the electron?

1915
01:23:16,686 --> 01:23:18,686
For example, in quantum electrodynamics.

1916
01:23:18,686 --> 01:23:20,686
And the answer is yes, but

1917
01:23:20,686 --> 01:23:22,686
only if you start with a mass.

1918
01:23:22,686 --> 01:23:24,686
What does a mass do?

1919
01:23:24,686 --> 01:23:27,186
A mass can be thought of

1920
01:23:27,186 --> 01:23:29,686
as a vertex in a Feynman diagram,

1921
01:23:29,686 --> 01:23:31,686
which does take left to right,

1922
01:23:31,686 --> 01:23:35,686
but the coefficient is proportional to the input mass.

1923
01:23:35,686 --> 01:23:38,686
So let me draw a Feynman diagram which does create,

1924
01:23:38,686 --> 01:23:41,686
which does shift the mass of the electron.

1925
01:23:41,686 --> 01:23:44,686
All you have to do is,

1926
01:23:46,686 --> 01:23:49,686
emit and absorb a photon,

1927
01:23:49,686 --> 01:23:52,686
but in the middle here,

1928
01:23:52,686 --> 01:23:55,686
have one of these mass insertions,

1929
01:23:55,686 --> 01:23:59,686
which itself flips from left to right.

1930
01:23:59,686 --> 01:24:01,686
Then you can start with left,

1931
01:24:01,686 --> 01:24:04,686
emitting the photon takes you to right,

1932
01:24:04,686 --> 01:24:08,686
but then the mass term takes you back to left,

1933
01:24:08,686 --> 01:24:10,686
and then, oh sorry, I didn't do that right.

1934
01:24:10,686 --> 01:24:12,686
Left goes to left,

1935
01:24:12,686 --> 01:24:14,686
and then the mass term takes left to right,

1936
01:24:14,686 --> 01:24:16,686
and then right to right.

1937
01:24:16,686 --> 01:24:23,686
The value of this Feynman diagram contains two factors,

1938
01:24:23,686 --> 01:24:25,686
or three factors.

1939
01:24:25,686 --> 01:24:28,686
It contains the electric charge twice.

1940
01:24:28,686 --> 01:24:31,686
Remember, the Feynman diagram for the emission of a photon

1941
01:24:31,686 --> 01:24:34,686
is proportional to the electric charge.

1942
01:24:34,686 --> 01:24:37,686
The coupling constant is the electric charge.

1943
01:24:37,686 --> 01:24:40,186
So this kind of Feynman diagram

1944
01:24:40,186 --> 01:24:42,686
would have the electric charge squared,

1945
01:24:42,686 --> 01:24:45,686
but it also has the original starting mass.

1946
01:24:46,686 --> 01:24:49,686
Original starting mass.

1947
01:24:49,686 --> 01:24:52,686
Let's call it m naught.

1948
01:24:52,686 --> 01:24:56,686
So we see that the shift in the mass

1949
01:24:56,686 --> 01:24:58,686
is proportional to the mass itself.

1950
01:24:58,686 --> 01:25:00,186
So now we can write down

1951
01:25:00,186 --> 01:25:01,686
that the mass of the electron

1952
01:25:01,686 --> 01:25:04,686
will consist of m naught,

1953
01:25:04,686 --> 01:25:08,686
plus something of order e squared times m naught,

1954
01:25:08,686 --> 01:25:11,686
plus more complicated diagrams,

1955
01:25:11,686 --> 01:25:14,686
e to the fourth times m naught.

1956
01:25:14,686 --> 01:25:15,686
In such a way,

1957
01:25:15,686 --> 01:25:18,686
that if the starting mass was zero to begin with,

1958
01:25:18,686 --> 01:25:20,686
it would remain zero.

1959
01:25:20,686 --> 01:25:22,686
The implication of that is that

1960
01:25:22,686 --> 01:25:24,686
not if the starting mass was zero

1961
01:25:24,686 --> 01:25:26,686
that it would remain zero,

1962
01:25:26,686 --> 01:25:29,686
it's that if the starting mass was very small,

1963
01:25:29,686 --> 01:25:31,686
it would remain small.

1964
01:25:31,686 --> 01:25:33,686
You would still ask the question,

1965
01:25:33,686 --> 01:25:35,686
why is the electron so

1966
01:25:35,686 --> 01:25:37,686
light compared to some fundamental scale,

1967
01:25:37,686 --> 01:25:40,686
but at least you wouldn't have this fine-tuning problem.

1968
01:25:40,686 --> 01:25:43,686
You would not be canceling out

1969
01:25:43,686 --> 01:25:48,686
differences between large numbers to make a small number.

1970
01:25:48,686 --> 01:25:50,686
You'd say, for reasons I don't know,

1971
01:25:50,686 --> 01:25:53,686
the mass of the electron may be small,

1972
01:25:53,686 --> 01:25:57,686
and all the corrections to it are even smaller.

1973
01:25:57,686 --> 01:26:00,686
So fermions are, in that sense,

1974
01:26:00,686 --> 01:26:03,686
better behaved than

1975
01:26:03,686 --> 01:26:08,686
scalar particles.

1976
01:26:08,686 --> 01:26:10,686
What about gauge bosons?

1977
01:26:10,686 --> 01:26:12,686
Well, gauge bosons have the same problem.

1978
01:26:12,686 --> 01:26:14,686
They have the same property,

1979
01:26:14,686 --> 01:26:16,686
that if they start out massless,

1980
01:26:16,686 --> 01:26:17,686
I won't go into it,

1981
01:26:17,686 --> 01:26:18,686
if they start out massless,

1982
01:26:18,686 --> 01:26:21,686
they remain massless to all orders.

1983
01:26:21,686 --> 01:26:23,686
So what that means

1984
01:26:23,686 --> 01:26:25,686
is that to understand the

1985
01:26:25,686 --> 01:26:27,686
mass scales of the standard model,

1986
01:26:27,686 --> 01:26:28,686
the fine-tuning problem,

1987
01:26:28,686 --> 01:26:31,686
there's really only one fine-tuning problem.

1988
01:26:31,686 --> 01:26:34,686
It's the fine-tuning that's associated with the Higgs boson.

1989
01:26:34,686 --> 01:26:36,686
If you get that one right,

1990
01:26:36,686 --> 01:26:38,686
all the other ones will be okay,

1991
01:26:38,686 --> 01:26:41,686
because all the other masses are direct responses

1992
01:26:41,686 --> 01:26:44,686
to the shift of the Higgs field.

1993
01:26:44,686 --> 01:26:45,686
Where is it?

1994
01:26:45,686 --> 01:26:46,686
I don't know.

1995
01:26:46,686 --> 01:26:48,686
We erased it, I guess.

1996
01:26:48,686 --> 01:26:49,686
Yeah.

1997
01:26:49,686 --> 01:26:51,686
To the shift of the Higgs field.

1998
01:26:51,686 --> 01:26:54,686
And if the shift of the Higgs field is controlled,

1999
01:26:54,686 --> 01:26:58,686
and if it doesn't undergo this enormous renormalization

2000
01:26:58,686 --> 01:27:00,686
and shift off to some huge amount,

2001
01:27:00,686 --> 01:27:03,686
then everything else will be okay.

2002
01:27:03,686 --> 01:27:05,686
There will be no other fine-tunings.

2003
01:27:05,686 --> 01:27:09,686
The only fine-tuning in the standard model,

2004
01:27:09,686 --> 01:27:11,686
no, really,

2005
01:27:11,686 --> 01:27:13,686
crazy fine-tuning,

2006
01:27:13,686 --> 01:27:15,686
the only really crazy fine-tuning

2007
01:27:15,686 --> 01:27:18,686
is the mass term from the Higgs boson,

2008
01:27:18,686 --> 01:27:22,686
which has to be about 38 orders of magnitude smaller

2009
01:27:22,686 --> 01:27:27,686
than whatever fundamental scale you might envision.

2010
01:27:30,686 --> 01:27:33,686
That's the great puzzle

2011
01:27:33,686 --> 01:27:36,686
that supersymmetry

2012
01:27:36,686 --> 01:27:38,686
and other kinds of theories like that

2013
01:27:38,686 --> 01:27:40,686
are intended to address.

2014
01:27:41,686 --> 01:27:43,686
Roughly speaking,

2015
01:27:43,686 --> 01:27:44,686
the question is,

2016
01:27:44,686 --> 01:27:46,686
is there any kind of context

2017
01:27:46,686 --> 01:27:52,686
where the Higgs boson cannot get a mass correction

2018
01:27:52,686 --> 01:27:53,686
which is enormously large?

2019
01:27:53,686 --> 01:27:55,686
Is there any kind of theory

2020
01:27:55,686 --> 01:27:57,686
where the Higgs boson itself

2021
01:27:57,686 --> 01:27:59,686
will also be a particle

2022
01:27:59,686 --> 01:28:02,686
whose mass isn't driven to enormously large values

2023
01:28:02,686 --> 01:28:04,686
by renormalization?

2024
01:28:04,686 --> 01:28:06,686
And so the answer is yes, we know some.

2025
01:28:11,686 --> 01:28:13,686
There's one other fine-tuning,

2026
01:28:13,686 --> 01:28:15,686
extreme fine-tuning in physics.

2027
01:28:15,686 --> 01:28:17,686
It only comes into play, though,

2028
01:28:17,686 --> 01:28:19,686
when you start thinking about gravity.

2029
01:28:19,686 --> 01:28:20,686
Before you think about gravity,

2030
01:28:20,686 --> 01:28:22,686
if you don't think about gravity,

2031
01:28:22,686 --> 01:28:24,686
then it's not a problem.

2032
01:28:24,686 --> 01:28:28,686
It is a problem that's associated with renormalization,

2033
01:28:28,686 --> 01:28:31,186
and it's the problem of

2034
01:28:31,186 --> 01:28:33,686
the renormalization of vacuum energy.

2035
01:28:33,686 --> 01:28:39,686
Renormalization of vacuum energy

2036
01:28:39,686 --> 01:28:41,686
is also a serious problem.

2037
01:28:41,686 --> 01:28:49,686
It's also a thing of very serious need for fine-tuning.

2038
01:28:49,686 --> 01:28:51,686
And I'll just tell you what it is

2039
01:28:51,686 --> 01:28:53,686
since we're dealing with fine-tuning.

2040
01:28:53,686 --> 01:28:56,686
First of all,

2041
01:28:56,686 --> 01:28:59,686
what the energy of the vacuum is,

2042
01:28:59,686 --> 01:29:02,686
for most purposes in physics, doesn't matter.

2043
01:29:02,686 --> 01:29:04,686
Why not?

2044
01:29:04,686 --> 01:29:07,686
Well, it's an additive constant to all energies.

2045
01:29:07,686 --> 01:29:09,686
If empty space has a vacuum,

2046
01:29:09,686 --> 01:29:10,686
it's energy, so be it.

2047
01:29:10,686 --> 01:29:12,686
But then as long as when you add a particle,

2048
01:29:12,686 --> 01:29:14,686
it adds the right amount of energy,

2049
01:29:14,686 --> 01:29:15,686
that's okay.

2050
01:29:15,686 --> 01:29:18,686
Who cares what the vacuum energy is?

2051
01:29:18,686 --> 01:29:20,686
It doesn't play any role in physics.

2052
01:29:20,686 --> 01:29:23,686
The real point is that only energy differences

2053
01:29:23,686 --> 01:29:25,686
are important in physics.

2054
01:29:25,686 --> 01:29:26,686
Energy differences.

2055
01:29:26,686 --> 01:29:29,686
So when you think about the mass of the electron,

2056
01:29:29,686 --> 01:29:32,686
don't think about it as the energy of electron.

2057
01:29:32,686 --> 01:29:34,686
Think about it as the extra energy

2058
01:29:34,686 --> 01:29:36,686
that you have to add to the vacuum.

2059
01:29:36,686 --> 01:29:38,686
Whatever the vacuum energy is,

2060
01:29:38,686 --> 01:29:40,686
you have to add a little energy

2061
01:29:40,686 --> 01:29:42,686
when you add an electron.

2062
01:29:42,686 --> 01:29:43,686
So it's energy differences.

2063
01:29:43,686 --> 01:29:45,686
The energy difference between the energy of an electron

2064
01:29:45,686 --> 01:29:47,686
and the energy of a vacuum,

2065
01:29:47,686 --> 01:29:49,186
which is really what we

2066
01:29:49,186 --> 01:29:50,686
call the mass of the electron.

2067
01:29:50,686 --> 01:29:53,686
So who cares then if the vacuum

2068
01:29:53,686 --> 01:29:55,686
gets its energy shifted by a large amount

2069
01:29:55,686 --> 01:29:59,686
as long as everything else gets shifted along with it?

2070
01:29:59,686 --> 01:30:02,686
So let's come back to who cares in a minute,

2071
01:30:02,686 --> 01:30:04,686
but let's just ask what

2072
01:30:04,686 --> 01:30:06,686
does happen to the vacuum energy.

2073
01:30:06,686 --> 01:30:08,686
And the vacuum energy is,

2074
01:30:08,686 --> 01:30:13,686
is something which is also renormalized,

2075
01:30:13,686 --> 01:30:16,686
and it's renormalized by diagrams

2076
01:30:16,686 --> 01:30:20,686
which have no input and no output particles.

2077
01:30:20,686 --> 01:30:23,686
In other words, just vacuum to vacuum.

2078
01:30:23,686 --> 01:30:26,686
The effect of such diagrams is to renormalize

2079
01:30:26,686 --> 01:30:28,686
the energy of the vacuum,

2080
01:30:28,686 --> 01:30:29,686
but who cares?

2081
01:30:29,686 --> 01:30:33,686
I mean, the vacuum energy is of no physical significance,

2082
01:30:33,686 --> 01:30:35,686
but nevertheless, let's ask what it looks like.

2083
01:30:35,686 --> 01:30:38,686
So for example, in the 5-4th theory,

2084
01:30:38,686 --> 01:30:40,686
let's do the 5-4th theory,

2085
01:30:40,686 --> 01:30:42,686
so there are, oh, yeah,

2086
01:30:42,686 --> 01:30:46,686
let's draw a diagram from the 5-4th theory

2087
01:30:46,686 --> 01:30:49,686
that involves no in particles and no out particles,

2088
01:30:49,686 --> 01:30:51,686
just vacuum to vacuum.

2089
01:30:51,686 --> 01:30:53,686
Here it is.

2090
01:30:58,686 --> 01:31:01,686
Four particles at the vertex here,

2091
01:31:01,686 --> 01:31:02,686
and that's it.

2092
01:31:02,686 --> 01:31:04,686
How big is that diagram?

2093
01:31:04,686 --> 01:31:05,686
Numerically, how big is it?

2094
01:31:05,686 --> 01:31:07,686
Well, it contains lambda,

2095
01:31:08,686 --> 01:31:11,686
and then it contains a propagator from here

2096
01:31:11,686 --> 01:31:13,686
back to the same place.

2097
01:31:13,686 --> 01:31:16,686
That's a factor of 1 over delta squared.

2098
01:31:16,686 --> 01:31:19,686
After I, it's a factor of 1 over delta squared

2099
01:31:19,686 --> 01:31:22,686
if this little separation here is of order delta,

2100
01:31:22,686 --> 01:31:23,686
but then there's another one here,

2101
01:31:23,686 --> 01:31:25,686
which is another 1 over delta squared,

2102
01:31:25,686 --> 01:31:27,186
so the whole thing is

2103
01:31:27,186 --> 01:31:28,686
1 over delta to the 4th.

2104
01:31:30,686 --> 01:31:33,686
Every diagram that you can write down

2105
01:31:33,686 --> 01:31:35,686
will typically go as 1 over delta to the 4th

2106
01:31:35,686 --> 01:31:37,686
times, there are more complicated ones,

2107
01:31:37,686 --> 01:31:39,186
but they'll also go as

2108
01:31:39,186 --> 01:31:40,686
1 over delta to the 4th,

2109
01:31:40,686 --> 01:31:43,686
and so the vacuum energy is also something

2110
01:31:43,686 --> 01:31:45,686
that gets renormalized.

2111
01:31:45,686 --> 01:31:47,686
Because it gets renormalized,

2112
01:31:47,686 --> 01:31:49,186
it means that if you

2113
01:31:49,186 --> 01:31:50,686
really want it to be 0,

2114
01:31:50,686 --> 01:31:53,686
you better fine-tune it to very high precision,

2115
01:31:53,686 --> 01:31:55,686
but on the other hand, who cares what it is?

2116
01:31:55,686 --> 01:31:56,686
We don't care what it is.

2117
01:31:56,686 --> 01:31:57,686
We don't care what it is

2118
01:31:57,686 --> 01:31:59,686
until gravity becomes important,

2119
01:31:59,686 --> 01:32:04,686
and the reason is that in standard theory,

2120
01:32:04,686 --> 01:32:07,686
the source of the gravitational field is 0,

2121
01:32:07,686 --> 01:32:09,686
and that's because the vacuum has energy.

2122
01:32:09,686 --> 01:32:11,686
If the vacuum has energy,

2123
01:32:11,686 --> 01:32:13,686
it means that the vacuum itself,

2124
01:32:13,686 --> 01:32:15,686
empty space, gravitates.

2125
01:32:15,686 --> 01:32:17,686
We're not going to go into this now,

2126
01:32:17,686 --> 01:32:19,686
this of course has to do with dark energy,

2127
01:32:19,686 --> 01:32:21,686
it has to do with the cosmological constant,

2128
01:32:21,686 --> 01:32:23,686
we'll talk about it another time,

2129
01:32:23,686 --> 01:32:25,686
but yes, this is also something

2130
01:32:25,686 --> 01:32:27,686
that has to be fine-tuned,

2131
01:32:27,686 --> 01:32:29,686
and it has to be fine-tuned once again

2132
01:32:29,686 --> 01:32:31,686
to enormously high precision.

2133
01:32:31,686 --> 01:32:34,686
So really, strictly speaking,

2134
01:32:34,686 --> 01:32:36,686
there are two fine-tuning problems in physics,

2135
01:32:36,686 --> 01:32:37,686
at least two.

2136
01:32:37,686 --> 01:32:39,686
Two that we know about.

2137
01:32:39,686 --> 01:32:42,686
One of them is the vacuum energy,

2138
01:32:42,686 --> 01:32:44,686
which has to be tuned to something like

2139
01:32:44,686 --> 01:32:47,686
123 decimal places,

2140
01:32:47,686 --> 01:32:51,686
and the other is the Higgs mass,

2141
01:32:51,686 --> 01:32:53,686
which only has to be tuned to something like

2142
01:32:53,686 --> 01:32:55,686
30 or 35 decimal places,

2143
01:32:55,686 --> 01:32:57,686
or something like that.

2144
01:32:57,686 --> 01:32:58,686
These are the two problems,

2145
01:32:58,686 --> 01:33:00,686
in many respects,

2146
01:33:00,686 --> 01:33:04,686
these are the sort of biggest puzzles

2147
01:33:04,686 --> 01:33:06,686
in particle physics at the present time,

2148
01:33:06,686 --> 01:33:10,686
of course it may turn out that these puzzles

2149
01:33:10,686 --> 01:33:13,686
are simply due to a misstatement of the problem.

2150
01:33:13,686 --> 01:33:16,686
You know, it often happens that really,

2151
01:33:16,686 --> 01:33:18,686
really thorny puzzles go away

2152
01:33:18,686 --> 01:33:20,686
when you state the problem correctly,

2153
01:33:20,686 --> 01:33:22,686
